('treatment with Obatoclax', 'sensitizes', 'GSC cultures')

The co-treatment with Obatoclax resulted in a significant reduction in cell viability compared to the combination treatment of RTx and SAHA without Obatoclax.

However the effect sizes of triple treatment were small, since the ATP-levels at day eight show that either HDACi/Obatoclax, Obatoclax/RTx or HDACi/RTx already inhibited the largest part of the cell population.

In the patient-derived GSC cultures GS257, GS274, GS224 and GS401, the effect sizes ranged from 5-9% and the enhancement factor ranged from 1.1 – 2.2 (GS257 and GS274 shown in Figure ).
