DISCUSSION

The present study emphasizes the efficacy of the Bcl-2 family pathway inhibition by Obatoclax in sensitizing patient-derived GSC cultures to HDACi/RTx, and hereby provides a circumvention for a tumor-related resistance mechanism to treatment.
('study', 'emphasizes', 'efficacy of family pathway')
('study', 'provides', 'circumvention for resistance mechanism to treatment')

The Bcl-2 family proteins are heterogeneously expressed in glioblastoma as about 30%[] to 60%[] shows over-representation of these proteins.[-] Moreover, Bcl-XL levels in patient-derived GSC cultures have shown a relationship with resistance to HDACi/RTx response.[] Here, we demonstrate that Obatoclax acted synergistically with HDACi and show efficacy in a large set of patient-derived glioblastoma cultures.
('family proteins', 'are expressed in', 'glioblastoma')

Hereby we confirm that this pathway is an adequate target to obtain treatment responses.
('pathway', 'is', 'target to obtain treatment responses')

The use of the serum-free patient-derived GSC culture model allowed to study resistance and tumor response mechanisms in a more representative manner than in immortalized glioma cell lines.[] Importantly, this model provides a tool to develop predictive profiles of treatment response.
('use of GSC culture model', 'allowed to study', 'resistance tumor response mechanisms')

The efficacy of down-regulation of Bcl-2 and Bcl-XL in inducing spontaneous cell death was already shown before.[] This efficacy depended on neither MGMT promoter methylation status nor recurrence.

A number of genes was found to be related to treatment response of patient-derived GSC cultures to combination treatments.
('number of genes', 'was found to be related to', 'treatment response of GSC cultures')

Others showed that the gene FBXW7 was related to SAHA-induced cell death and Bcl-2 inhibition.[] This points to a biological rationale in Mcl-1 functioning to be predictive of treatment response to LBH589/Obatoclax.

The use of these genes as potential markers for patient stratification or the functionality of these genes in sensitivity to combination treatments should be explored in future studies.
('use of genes', 'should be explored in', 'studies')

Others have studied the relationship between HDACi and Bcl-2 family proteins before.
('Others', 'have studied', 'relationship between HDACi family proteins')

A recent study has shown that the intact PTEN immortalized malignant glioma cell lines are susceptible to the combination of SAHA and the Bcl-2 inhibitors ABT-737, whereas PTEN mutations were not.[] They also showed that inhibition of the PTEN/PI3K pathway by BKM-120 sensitized glioma cells for ABT-737.[] The patient-derived GSC model we used in this study is known to harbor PTEN deletions due to loss of chromosome 10q [, ], and ensures that we tested the treatment efficacy in a setting of hyper-activation of the PIK3-pathway.
('PTEN glioma cell lines', 'are susceptible to', 'combination of SAHA')

Therefore, this suggests that Obatoclax is a more potent combination partner for HDACi in PTEN deleted tumors than ABT-737.
('Obatoclax', 'is', 'combination partner for HDACi in PTEN tumors')

The main differences between Obatoclax and ABT-737 are the stronger induction of autophagy[] and the stronger inhibition of Mcl-1 by the first drug.
('differences between Obatoclax', 'are', 'induction of autophagy')

Both can be underlying the efficacy in PTEN deleted tumors.[] Earlier, the efficacy of SAHA was related to Mcl-1 levels in acute myeloid leukemia.[] Another study showed that in diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, over-expression of Bcl-2 and Bcl-XL triggered resistance to the HDACi SAHA and Trichostatin A, whereas the Bcl-2 family inhibitor ABT-737 increased sensitivity to SAHA treatment.

Also, this study showed that the least sensitive cells to SAHA showed up-regulation of Bcl-XL and Mcl-1 proteins.[] The loss of pro-apoptotic Bcl-2 family proteins Bax or Bax/Bak ratios are related to insensitivity to HDACi in Burkitt's lymphoma in a predictive and functional sense.

[] In mantle cell lymphoma, the efficacy of SAHA was enhanced by the BH-3 mimetic ABT-263.[] In contrast, another study did not find HDACi efficacy to be related to Bcl-2 family proteins.[] Thus, these relationships between Bcl-2 family proteins and HDACi responses are either tumor type or HDACi specific.

Our study shows that inhibition of the Bcl-XL and Mcl-1 proteins by Obatoclax is related to efficacy of SAHA alone or in combination with RTx.
('inhibition of proteins', 'is related to', 'efficacy of SAHA')

We observed restored levels of Bcl-2 family proteins Bcl-XL and Mcl-1, occurring at 72 hours after Obatoclax, HDACi and HDACi/RTx treatments.

This observation indicates that Bcl-2 family members are restored within this time frame, if these are not inhibited effectively.
('family members', 'are restored within', 'time frame')

This in turn can contribute to resistance to treatment.

As a mechanism of action, HDACi have shown to be able to down-regulate Bcl-2 family members, however not in all heterogeneous tumors including glioblastoma.

[] Others suggest that the up-regulation of pro-apoptotic members by HDACi are neutralized by high levels of anti-apoptotic members such as Bcl-2 and Bcl-XL.[] In squamous cell carcinoma Mcl-1 was related to resistance to the BH3-mimetic ABT-737.

The HDACi SAHA has the ability to synergize with this drug by shuttling the Bcl-2 family protein Bim from Mcl-1 to Bcl-2/Bcl-XL.[]
('HDACi SAHA', 'has', 'ability to synergize with drug')

Not only does Obatoclax enhance the efficacy of HDACi/RTx, it also enhanced the efficacy of RTx as treatment alone.
('Obatoclax', 'does enhance', 'efficacy of HDACi/RTx')

Thus, in many treatment modalities, including conventional glioblastoma treatment such as RTx, the Bcl-2 family members may play a crucial role.
('family members', 'may play', 'role')

Others have shown already that Bcl-2 family members are determinants of responsiveness to treatment in glioblastoma.
('family members', 'are', 'determinants of responsiveness to treatment in glioblastoma')

Bcl-XL levels were related to radioresistance in glioma [] and Mcl-1 proteins regulate temozolomide efficacy in glioma independently of MGMT promoter methylation status.[] Here, we found that MGMT promoter methylation status and tumor recurrence, which normally determine patient overall outcome[], were not related to the applied treatments either.
('proteins', 'regulate', 'temozolomide efficacy in glioma')
('levels', 'were related to', 'radioresistance in glioma')

Thus, our results are unlikely to be determined by these tumor statuses a priori.
('results', 'are unlikely to be determined by', 'tumor statuses')

The effect sizes of both SAHA and LBH589 in combination with Obatoclax correlated to expression levels of specific genes.
('effect sizes of SAHA', 'correlated to', 'expression levels of genes')

Gene profiles may provide an opportunity to include predictive decision variables in treatment and patient selection.
('Gene profiles', 'may provide', 'opportunity to include decision variables in treatment')

This may be of clinical relevance specifically for the MGMT un-methylated tumors.

We need to point out immediately that these gene sets need further exploration in in vivo settings to be validated.
('gene', 'sets', 'need to be validated')

Although these gene sets do not necessarily implicate mechanisms of action of the proposed treatments, they may provide insight into resistance mechanisms.
('gene sets', 'do not implicate', 'mechanisms of action of treatments')

FBXW7, the gene associated with LBH589/Obatoclax response, was shown to have a relationship with response to SAHA before, as well as to Bcl-2 inhibition.

Both FBXW7 and Bcl-2 inhibition were predictive for efficacy of SAHA in squamous cell carcinoma.

Mutated FBXW7 sensitized cells to HDACi and stabilized Mcl-1.[] FBXW7 encodes for the protein ubiquitin protein ligase and is positively related with the effect size of LBH589/Obatoclax in our study.

Obatoclax has the potency to inhibit Mcl-1, and is more effective in combination with LBH589 in tumors that highly express FBXW7.
('Obatoclax', 'has', 'potency to inhibit')
('Obatoclax', 'is effective in', 'combination with LBH589 in tumors')

Moreover, the whole gene set which was related to LBH589/Obatoclax response was associated with cell cycle and cell death and survival mechanisms, represented by the four genes FBXW7, VIP, FOXK1 and PCDHGB6.
('gene', 'was associated with', 'cell cycle')

This was also true for the gene ubiquilin 1 (UBQLN1), which was associated to SAHA/Obatoclax response.

This gene functions in cell death and survival as well.
('gene', 'functions in', 'cell death')

In addition, response to RTx/Obatoclax was associated to genes that function in the cell cycle and cellular proliferation as well.
('response to RTx/Obatoclax', 'was associated to', 'genes')

Basic studies should be performed to assess the direct relationship between the function of these genes and the success rate of Obatoclax, but the genes provide insights into the process of cellular responses.
('genes', 'provide', 'insights into process of responses')
('studies', 'should be performed to assess', 'relationship between function of genes')

Our data on cell regulation by caspase-3/7 and autophagy are therefore potentially important mechanisms of action in the response to combination treatment.
('data on cell regulation', 'are', 'mechanisms of action')

In summary, this study underlines the potential of inhibiting the Bcl-2 family proteins in combination treatment with HDACi and HDACi/RTx.
('study', 'underlines', 'potential of inhibiting family proteins')

Potential toxicities of combination therapies which may limit clinical use should be explored further.

Examples could be thrombocytopenia by inhibition of Bcl-XL[] and HDACi.[] Furthermore, we obtained predictive gene profiles that are associated with cellular regulatory functions for the combination treatments with Obatoclax.
('Examples', 'be', 'thrombocytopenia by inhibition')

These gene sets may aid in selecting the tumors most responsive to treatment.
('gene sets', 'may aid in', 'selecting tumors')

MATERIALS &amp; METHODS

Chemicals

Stocks of 50mM SAHA (Cayman chemicals, MI, USA), 200μM LBH589 (Biovision, CA, USA) and 60mM Obatoclax (Selleck Chemicals, Texas, USA) were prepared in dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO, Sigma-Aldrich, MO, USA) and stored at −20°C.
('Stocks of SAHA', 'were prepared in', 'sulfoxide')
('Stocks of SAHA', 'stored at', 'C.')
('200mM LBH589', 'were prepared in', 'sulfoxide')
('200mM LBH589', 'stored at', 'C.')
('60mM Obatoclax', 'were prepared in', 'sulfoxide')
('60mM Obatoclax', 'stored at', 'C.')

Staurosporin was obtained from BioMol, Germany.
('Staurosporin', 'was obtained from', 'BioMol')

Patient-derived glioblastoma stem-like cell cultures

Fresh glioblastoma tissue was obtained from patients undergoing surgery at the Department of Neurosurgery, ErasmusMC (Rotterdam, The Netherlands) after informed consent and approval by the institution's medical ethical board.
('glioblastoma tissue', 'was obtained from', 'patients undergoing surgery')

The tissue was dissociated mechanically and enzymatically, after which the patient-derived GSC cultures were cultured under serum-free conditions in DMEM/F12 medium supplemented with 2% B27 (Life Technologies, UK), 20ng/ml bFGF, 20ng/ml EGF (Tebu-Bio, France), 5ug/ml heparin (Sigma-Aldrich, MO, USA) as was described previously.[] These patient-derived GSC cultures, which were characterized and validated as previously reported.[] The U373 cells were cultures under 10% serum conditions in DMEM medium.
('GSC cultures', 'were cultured under', 'conditions in DMEM/F12 medium supplemented with B27')

The cultures were stored at 37 °C in a humid 95% air/5% CO2 chamber.
('cultures', 'were stored at', 'C')

In total, nineteen patient-derived GSC cultures were used for the experiments.
('GSC cultures', 'were used for', 'experiments')

Viability assay

Concentration-response assays were performed in order to determine IC50 values of Obatoclax.

The cells of various GSC cultures were plated at 1×103 cells/well in 96-wells plates.
('cells of GSC cultures', 'were plated at', 'x')

After incubation overnight, various drug concentrations in three-fold increments were applied to the cells.
('drug concentrations in increments', 'were applied to', 'cells')

At five and eight days post-treatment cell viability was measured using the CellTiter-Glo assay (Promega, WI, USA).

The results were plotted and the IC50 values were computed using the median effect equation.[] The IC50 values of the HDACi SAHA and LBH59 in the GSC cultures GS79 and GS257 were derived from previous research.[] Subsequently, Chou-Talalay assays were performed on the GSC cultures GS79 and GS257 for Obatoclax in combination with the HDACi to determine synergy.[] After assessment of the combination effects in these two cultures, either two or four concentrations (10, 30, 100 and 225nM) were applied to the panel of patient-derived GSC cultures to determine the combination effects.
('results', 'were computed using', 'effect equation')
('IC50 values', 'were computed using', 'effect equation')

From these concentrations, an estimated IC50 was calculated for each glioblastoma culture.

The HDACi concentrations were always kept similar at 1μM SAHA and 20nM LBH589.
('HDACi concentrations', 'were kept similar at', '1mM SAHA')

The DMSO concentration was never above 1% in the dilutions.

RTx (3Gy) was applied as single-fraction treatment from a Cesium-137 source 24 hours after drug application.
('RTx', 'was applied as', 'treatment from source')

Western blot

Alteration of specific proteins post-treatment was determined by seeding cells of the GSC culture GS257 in culture flasks with 225nM Obatoclax, 1 μM SAHA and the combination.
('Alteration of proteins', 'was determined by', 'seeding cells of GSC culture GS257 in culture flasks')

After 24 hours, the cells were irradiated with 3Gy.
('cells', 'were irradiated with', '3Gy')

At 24 and 48 hours post-RTx, the cells were harvested, washed with PBS and collected in a 1% Triton-X100 (Sigma-Aldrich) buffer for protein isolation.
('cells', 'washed with', 'PBS')

Protein concentrations were measured with the BCA Protein Assay Reagent Kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific, MA, USA).
('Protein concentrations', 'were measured with', 'BCA Protein Assay Reagent Kit')

Protein separation was performed on a 4-15% pre-casted gel (Bio-Rad, CA, USA), and blotted onto a PVDF membrane (Immobilon-P, Millipore, MA, USA) using the Mini-Protean Tetra Cell system (Bio-Rad).
('Protein separation', 'was performed on', 'gel')
('Protein separation', 'blotted onto', 'PVDF membrane')

After blocking the membranes with 5% non-fatty milk solution for 30 minutes at room temperature, the blots were incubated with primary antibodies against Bcl-XL, LC3BI/II, Mcl-1 (1:375, Cell Signalling, MA, USA) and anti-β-actin (1:5,000, Millipore) in 5% BSA/TBS-T overnight.
('blots', 'were incubated with', 'antibodies')

Membranes were washed with TBS-T 0.2% and incubated with secondary antibodies, anti-rabbit-HRP and anti-mouse-HRP (1:2000, Dako Denmark A/S, Denmark) 1½h at room temperature and detected by chemiluminescence using the Pierce ECL substrate (Thermo Fisher Scientific) and the ChemiDoc MP system (BioRad).
('Membranes', 'were washed with', '%')
('Membranes', 'incubated with', 'antibodies')

The data were analyzed using the ImageLab software (Bio-rad).
('data', 'were analyzed using', 'ImageLab software')

Caspase-3/7 assay

The GS257 GSC cultures were seeded at 5×103 cells/well in a black 96-wells plate and incubated with the treatment as performed in the viability and Western blot experiments (SAHA, Obatoclax, after 24 hours RTx).
('GS257 GSC cultures', 'were seeded at', 'x')
('GS257 GSC cultures', 'incubated with', 'treatment')

Immediately after RTx, the cells were incubated with 5μM of the kinetic apoptosis reagent of the CellPlayer 96-Well Kinetic Caspase-3/7 Apoptosis Assay (Essen Bioscience) and were live imaged by using the IncuCyte system (Essen BioScience) with a 10X objective at 37°C in a humid 95% air/5% CO2 chamber.
('cells', 'were incubated with', '5mM of apoptosis reagent')

The apoptosis-inducer staurosporin (20nM) was used as a positive control.
('staurosporin', 'was used as', 'control')

Three fluorescent images/well were collected up to 60 hours post-RTx.

The caspase-3/7 activity was presented as counted objects/mm2 as measured by the IncuCyte software.

Gene expression analysis

The RNA of the original glioblastoma tissue corresponding with the glioblastoma cultures was isolated with the RNeasy Mini kit (#74104, Qiagen Inc., CA, USA).
('RNA of glioblastoma tissue corresponding with glioblastoma cultures', 'was isolated with', 'RNeasy Mini kit')

The mRNA expression levels of were analysed by the HumanHT-12 v4 Expression BeadChip microarray (Illumina, CA, USA).
('mRNA expression levels', 'were analysed by', 'v4 Expression BeadChip microarray')

The raw intensity values of all the samples were normalized using quantile normalization with the Partek software, version 6.6 (Partek Inc., St. Louis, MO, USA).
('intensity values of samples', 'were normalized using', 'normalization')

Subsequently, the Partek Batch Remover was used to remove the effect of the differences between the batches.
('Partek Batch Remover', 'was used to remove', 'effect of differences between batches')

The effect sizes of HDACi/Obatoclax, and RTx/Obatoclax in n=13 GSC cultures (mRNA expression data of GS102 did not meet quality standards) were correlated to the gene expression levels.
('mRNA expression data of GS102', 'did not meet', 'quality standards')
('effect sizes of HDACi/Obatoclax', 'were correlated to', 'gene expression levels')
('RTx/Obatoclax in n GSC cultures', 'were correlated to', 'gene expression levels')

The data were analyzed using the linear model function in R package ‘stats’ (version 2.15.3) to identify genes that correlate to treatment responses (Pearson's R correlations).
('data', 'were analyzed using', 'model function in package stats')

The p-values were adjusted for multiple comparisons using the method of Benjamini &amp; Hochberg.

[] The cut-off values for significantly expressed genes were the adjusted p-values (p&lt;0.05).

The initially identified genes that significantly correlated with response were validated using a sample set of five additionally treated GSC cultures (p&lt;0.05).
('genes', 'were validated using', 'sample set of GSC cultures')

Heat maps of the genes were constructed by the OmniViz Treescape software.
('Heat maps of genes', 'were constructed by', 'OmniViz Treescape software')

The functional and network analyses of the identified genes were performed using the QIAGEN's Ingenuity® Pathway Analysis (IPA®, QIAGEN Redwood City, www.qiagen.com/ingenuity).
('analyses of genes', 'were performed using', 'Ingenuity Pathway Analysis')

Quantitative PCR on MGMT promoter methylation

The DNA of the various patient-derived GSC cultures was isolated and 100ng was used for the quantitative polymerase chain reaction (PCR).
('DNA of GSC cultures', 'was used for', 'polymerase chain reaction')

The DNAsamples were modified with sodium bisulphite using the EZ DNA Methylation GoldTM kit (Zymo Research, Baseclear, The Netherlands) Primers specific for methylated and un-methylated MGMT promoter DNA were used as described by others.[] Methylation specific primers were F: TTTCGACGTTCGTAGGTTTTCGC and R: GCACTCTTCCGAAAACGAAACG.
('DNAsamples', 'were modified with', 'sodium bisulphite using EZ DNA Methylation GoldTM kit')

The un-methylated specific primers were F: TTTGTGTTTTGATGTTTGTAGGTTTTTGT and R: AACTCCACACTCTTCCAAAAACAAAACAQ.
('primers', 'were', 'F')

The PCR conditions were used as described by others[], with annealing temperature of 59°C and 40 cycles of amplification yielding PCR products for methylated and un-methylated DNA of 80 and 93 base pairs, respectively.

The PCR products were separated on a routine 2% agarose gel.
('PCR products', 'were separated on', 'agarose gel')

As a methylated control the DNA isolated from FFPE human colorectal cancer cell line SW48 was used and FFPE human tonsil DNA was used as an un-methylated control.
('DNA isolated from FFPE cancer cell line SW48', 'was used as', 'control')
('FFPE tonsil DNA', 'was used as', 'control')

In addition, in each experiment a H2O sample without DNA was used as a negative contamination control.
('H2O sample without DNA', 'was used as', 'contamination control')

Statistical analysis

For the viability and caspase-3/7 assay experiments, the means of triplicates were plotted with the standard deviations.
('assay experiments', 'were plotted with', 'deviations')

The Western blots were performed in singlicate.
('Western blots', 'were performed in', 'singlicate')

The results were presented as a percentage of non-treated controls.
('results', 'were presented as', 'percentage of controls')

The differences between treatment effects were analyzed using the one-way ANOVA and the Tukey Post-Test for multiple conditions.
('differences between treatment effects', 'were analyzed using', 'ANOVA')

The statistical significance was defined as p&lt;0.05.
('significance', 'was defined as', 'p')

The differences in mean cell viability between combinations were presented as effect sizes.
('differences in cell viability between combinations', 'were presented as', 'effect sizes')

In addition, we calculated the enhancement factor of combination treatments, as was described by Chou.[] In case of an enhancement factors &gt; 1 in combination with p&lt;0.05, the combination was considered effective and the GSC was defined as a responder.

